Okay, this stuff is wild. Heavy blueberry, but a tart one. The raspberry nestles in well alongside this, and that "tropical" guava/pink grapefruit that is the pink guava is there and helping things along. The hops...yeah, that just makes everything gel. &#xD;
&#xD;
This is one of the best things i've ever tasted that has not existed until this moment.&#xD;
&#xD;
Seeing as this was my exact thoughts upon having Fiestas and Fiascos, I'd say you nailed the goal.&#xD;
&#xD;
Blueberry fans, fruit lovers, and people who dig what whole "what the hell is this deliciousness that should have been a thing" vibe? Mix this.&#xD;
&#xD;
Awesome stuff!

Don't let the old stale beer smell of the Yakima Hops or the pissed on carpet smell of the Pink Guava dissuade you. This recipe is fantastic and completely different than anything I've tried in a long time. The ingredient list may look like Kyle drunkenly tripped and fell into his flavor stash and then tried to play it off like he meant to do it by grabbing a handful of bottles and yelling "found em!" but this recipe is somehow fruity, but not overly fruity.  Slightly sweet but also sour, and floral but not overbearing and still full bodied.&#xD;
&#xD;
This hodgepodge of flavors reminds me of the spice girls. Without those five random singers a miracle never would have happened. A video of a topless Ginger Spice was leaked.&#xD;
&#xD;
This recipe is Ginger Spices boobs.
